				<text_box uid="842" x="3204.93" y="530.5" width="366" height="196">Missing features / To-Dos: 
- Urbanisation/coastal migration
- Might be good to have different investment options (investing in already existing dikes, or building new ones)
- There could be the option that dikes are not even maintained and then break down? Best to use this only when we actually account for well protected and badly protected areas.
- Currently the length of dikes stays constant, which is inconsistent, as the effective flood protection height, determines the length of how much is considered protected
- The people that retreat from the coast are more likely the ones that would be flooded, this should reduce the &quot;being flooded&quot; fraction, as people retreat, right?</text_box>
