	</model>
	<model name="Sea_level_rise_adaptation">
		<variables>
			<aux name="Annual\ncosts of\nflood protection\nmaintenance">
				<eqn>Average_flood_protection_construction_cost*Fraction_of_dike_construction_cost_for_maintenance_annually*Length_of_coastline_that_is_protected*Average_flood_protection_height*UNIT_metre</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Total investment to\nincrease flood\nprotection height">
				<eqn>Ability_to_invest_in_flood_protection
* Willingness_to_invest_in_flood_protection_1 
*Cost_of_raising_dikes_by_mismatch_of_SLR_and_flood_protection_height_in_protected_areas</eqn>
				<units>b$</units>
			</aux>
			<stock name="Average flood\nprotection height">
				<doc>First implementation: set this to 0 for the 1980 level of protection. If sea level increases, the current flood protection level gets negative, i.e. the protection is worse</doc>
				<eqn>Average_flood_protection_height_in_1980</eqn>
				<inflow>Increase_of_average_flood_protection_height_through_investment</inflow>
				<units>metre</units>
			</stock>
			<flow name="Increase of average\nflood protection height\nthrough investment" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<eqn>(SQRT(Average_flood_protection_height^2 + Effective_annual_investment_in_flood_protection_height*UNIT_year/(Length_of_coastline_that_is_protected*Average_flood_protection_construction_cost)) - Average_flood_protection_height)/UNIT_year</eqn>
				<units>metre/year</units>
			</flow>
			<aux name="Fraction of dike construction cost for maintenance annually">
				<eqn>0.02</eqn>
				<units>1/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Ability to invest\nin flood protection">
				<doc>Between 0 and 1</doc>
				<eqn>0.5</eqn>
				<units>1</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Annual loss of\ncapital for flood protection" access="output" isee:autocreated="true">
				<eqn>Length_of_coastline_that_is_protected*Average_value_of_land_used_up_by_flood_protection*Increase_of_average_flood_protection_height_through_investment*1.7*UNIT_metre_to_kilometre</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Average flood protection\nconstruction cost">
				<doc>For the beginning this is held constant in the absence of other information. Unit should theoretically be b$ per km coastline per m vertical elevation, but equation needs the &quot;m&quot; to be squared ?!

As described in CIAM documentation (https://github.com/delavane/CIAM) with reference to Hillen et al.: 

Hillen M, Jonkman S, Kanning W, Kok M, Geldenhuys M, Stive M (2010) Coastal defence cost estimates: Case study of the Netherlands, New Orleans and Vietnam. Communications on Hydraulic
and Geotechnical Engineering 1
</doc>
				<eqn>0.00602</eqn>
				<units>b$/metre/metre/km</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Average value of land used\nup by flood protection">
				<eqn>0.005367</eqn>
				<units>b$/km^2</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Average flood protection\nheight in 1980">
				<eqn>2.66</eqn>
				<units>metre</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Cost of raising dikes by mismatch of\nSLR and flood protection height\nin protected areas">
				<eqn>Average_flood_protection_construction_cost * Length_of_coastline_that_is_protected * 
((Expected_global_SLR_in_50_years+Average_flood_protection_height)^2 - Average_flood_protection_height^2)</eqn>
				<units>b$</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Time to increase flood protection height">
				<eqn>10</eqn>
				<units>year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Length of\ncoastline\nthat is\nprotected">
				<eqn>Total_length_of_coastline_in_DIVA / (Total_length_of_coastline_in_DIVA/Length_of_protected_coastlines_in_DIVA - 1 + EXP(Exponential_rate_of_fp_length_increase * (Average_flood_protection_height-Average_flood_protection_height_in_1980 - Effective_flood_height)) )</eqn>
				<units>km</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Effective annual investment\nin flood protection height">
				<eqn>Total_investment_to_increase_flood_protection_height/Time_to_increase_flood_protection_height</eqn>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="UNIT metre to kilometre">
				<eqn>0.001</eqn>
				<units>km/metre</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Length of protected coastlines in DIVA">
				<eqn>460143.2</eqn>
				<units>km</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="UNIT metre">
				<eqn>1</eqn>
				<units>metre</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="UNIT year">
				<eqn>1</eqn>
				<units>year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Expected global SLR\nin 50 years" access="input">
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>metre</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Total flood protection costs">
				<eqn>Annual_costs_of_flood_protection_maintenance + Annual_loss_of_capital_for_flood_protection + Effective_annual_investment_in_flood_protection_height</eqn>
				<isee:summing/>
				<units>b$/year</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Willingness to invest\nin flood protection 1" access="input">
				<eqn>0.25 {0, 1}</eqn>
				<units>1</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Total length of coastline in DIVA">
				<eqn>1038233.9</eqn>
				<units>km</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Exponential rate of fp length increase">
				<eqn>-3</eqn>
				<units>1/metre</units>
			</aux>
			<aux name="Effective flood height" access="input">
				<eqn>{Enter equation for use when not hooked up to other models}</eqn>
				<units>metre</units>
			</aux>
		</variables>
		<views>
			<style color="black" background="white" font_style="normal" font_weight="normal" text_decoration="none" text_align="center" vertical_text_align="center" font_color="black" font_family="Arial" font_size="10pt" padding="2" border_color="black" border_width="thin" border_style="none">
				<text_box color="black" background="white" text_align="left" vertical_text_align="top" font_size="12pt"/>
				<isee:loop_indicator color="black" background="white" text_align="left" vertical_text_align="top" font_size="12pt"/>
				<numeric_display color="white" background="white" font_size="12pt" border_width="thin" border_style="solid" isee:transparent="false" isee:show_divider="true" isee:show_bounding_box="true" label_side="left"/>
